Abdomen dark. Male tenth tergum (

Figs. 
14, 16

) in lateral view semicircular with straight dorsal margin; in dorsal view its apex slightly inflated. Aedeagus (

Figs. 
14 –15

) strongly sclerotized, narrow and elongate, in ventral view apical half strongly narrowing and slightly curved to right; in lateral view middle portion strongly inflated dorsally with apex slightly upcurved. Female eighth sternum broad with posterior margin strongly prominent; tenth tergum (

Fig. 
16

) digitiform with pointed tip, directed caudally; gonapophyses (

Fig. 
16

) directed dorsally, subquadrate with round tip.
